{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7bb7c24c-0767-4ca0-a096-599ad4bc8a0c","content":"Yes, you'll have compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2 and .NET Core 3.1**, but it **dropped support for `net5.0`** since .NET 5 is out of support.\n\nHere's the breakdown for your target frameworks:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ⚠️ May work but is out of support; MSTest v3 officially targets .NET 6+ for modern .NET |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported — .NET 5 reached end-of-life |\n\n**Recommended actions before migrating:**\n\n1. Replace `net5.0` with `net6.0` or `net8.0` (current LTS).\n2. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or `net8.0` (also end-of-life).\n3. Then upgrade to the MSTest v3 meta-package (`MSTest` version `3.x`), which replaces the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file with these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b2bf53bd-6542-44b7-9ad2-daf431711201","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"E3C2:1EA0D0:BB6D78:D51DF0:6A053C2E"},"id":"e14a9bd7-8675-4d74-a03e-5d52ef825f2a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:06:32.682Z","parentId":"51cc0391-acc9-4838-8bf3-dc9d67d3fdea"}
